This paper deals with the optimization of mixture models, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper specifically compares the performance of EM and GD algorithms in escaping one-cluster regions in two-component mixture models. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), and neural networks (cs.NE). However, given the focus on optimization algorithms and mixture models, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
